For many moons I have hunted the evil that plagues the lands of Norrath. For much of that time, it has been at Leetah's side.  We have fought, sweat, bled, cried, and cheered together for the Pack, and she will always be a dear friend to me. I understand this decision she has made all too well. The fight is a hard one and it takes its toll on you. <br>
<br>
When Leetah approached me about the decision she was making, I was a bit shocked when she asked me, as I would assume any would be. It is a great honor to have been considered, and I thank Leetah for her faith in me. However...I too am getting old in my years. To be honest, I don't know how many fights this Dwarf has left in him. There are other things in my life that have started to keep me away from the adventuring life. Perhaps the fact that my wife, Yonder, is not there to share in those adventures with me. Perhaps it is the still I keep in my private chambers deep within North Kaladim. Whatever the reasons, my Ale or my bride, the flame of youth is waning from this Paladin's eye...and I count the days until I meet Lord Brell in the halls of Underfoot. <br>
<br>
The rank of Packmaster is not for one such as me...one that is worn from years of battle. I would follow a Wolf to the ends of the Earth, and sacrifice my life to save their own. I am and always will be the protector of every Wolf that runs with the Pack and the champion of every cause, but Packmaster? No. With respect, I must decline.<br>
<br>
The rank of Packmaster calls for one who still feels the flames of youth blaze in their soul. Who is not afraid to lead, to accept responsibility, to listen to suggestion, and heed the advise of their Elders. As for Adlehardt, I have watched him for a long time. I have known him since he was a pup and helped raise him in the ways of the Aegis Wolf. He has come a long way since those days on the hills overlooking the Lake of Ill Omen. It was there that he found a chunk of dirt and called it &quot;Adle's Rock&quot;. But that rock is so much more than just a stone. It is a symbol of his determination, and his loyalty. He is always ready to come to the aid of any in need, and help those who are less fortunate. He has come a long way indeed...he has come of age, he has become a leader amongst the Wolves. For this old Dwarf, it was a hard decision. But I feel Adlehardt is up to the challenge, and will do all that he has to for the glory of the Pack.<br>
<br>
&lt;Kronenburg unsheathes Ghoulbane, and places it at Adlehardt's feet&gt;<br>
<br>
Lord Adlehardt, accept this as my approval of your succession. I have been and always will be your friend, and I will always help support and guide you in this new dawn for the Aegis Wolves of Tunare.<br>
<br>
I salute you, Packmaster Adlehardt.<br>
<br>
Kronenburg Ponykeg<br>
Husband to Yonder Wendobrayxe<br>
Paladin of Underfoot<br>
Bearer of the Shield<br>
Elder and Protector of the Pack  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003030><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub7.ezboard.com/ubovathunderflail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bova Thunderflail</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Jaded Flame</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(7/6/01 12:08:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub7.ezboard.com/faegiswolvestunarepack.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=613.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.velocity.net/~kayen/bova.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Mama Wolf calls you to the Guildhall.....</span><hr size=1> WOW!<br>
